subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnostic characters.
The species is separated from other members within the subgenus by the wing without marking, the squama with a few setae (
1–3
), the anal lobe extremely reduced, low AR (
0.33–0.59
), the high VR and the anal point without lateral projection.

Wing (
Figure 1 A
). VR 1.45–1.47 , 1.46 . R with 7 –10, 9 setae; R 1 with 4 –8, 6; R 4 + 5 with 13 –17, 14. Squama with 1 –3, 2 setae. Anal lobe extremely reduced, wing without marking.

Hypopygium (
Figure 1 C, D
). Tergite IX with 3 –5, 4 median setae. Laterosternite with 1 –2, 2 setae. Anal point broad, 36 –42, 38 µm long, without lateral projection. Phallapodeme 34 –42, 37 µm long; transverse sternapodeme 21 –23, 22 µm long. Gonocoxite 73 –86, 82 µm long. Superior volsella (
Figure 1 . C
) pad–like, expanded distally, with 2–3 short inner setae and 2 long setae on outer apical margin. Inferior volsella 52 –65, 61 µm long, gradually tapered from base to apex, with 5–7 oral setae and an apical seta. Gonostylus 73 –91, 81 µm long, with 3–4 long setae along inner margin. HR 0.95–1.11 , 1.03 . HV 1.72–2.12 , 1.92 .
